01:12:52,411 --> 01:12:54,152
Hey, shipmate!

522
01:12:58,548 --> 01:13:00,550
The infamous Uncle Ralph.

523
01:13:12,910 --> 01:13:15,565
[Sound of passing subway.]

524
01:13:27,141 --> 01:13:28,360
Dalisay!

525
01:13:32,277 --> 01:13:33,409
Dalisay!

526
01:13:33,931 --> 01:13:34,932
Come here.

527
01:13:39,937 --> 01:13:41,765
Sit down, over here.

528
01:13:43,680 --> 01:13:44,855
Don't worry.

529
01:13:45,508 --> 01:13:47,118
Come a little closer.

530
01:13:50,817 --> 01:13:52,993
Alright, close your eyes...

531
01:13:53,864 --> 01:13:55,692
Go on.
Don't worry.

532
01:13:56,780 --> 01:13:58,085
Give me your hand.

533
01:13:58,129 --> 01:14:00,174
I want you to feel something.

534
01:14:11,490 --> 01:14:13,013
You bought this for me?

535
01:14:14,798 --> 01:14:16,843
- You didn't have to do this.
- It's not real.

536
01:14:16,887 --> 01:14:18,497
It's cubic zirconia.

537
01:14:18,541 --> 01:14:20,586
But it's a sign
of things to come.

538
01:14:20,630 --> 01:14:23,459
I'm gonna get you the real one
as soon as I can.

539
01:14:24,155 --> 01:14:25,809
Thank you, it's beautiful.

540
01:14:27,724 --> 01:14:28,638
Another one?

541
01:14:28,681 --> 01:14:29,813
Go on, open it up.

542
01:14:37,081 --> 01:14:37,647
Try it on.

543
01:14:38,735 --> 01:14:40,345
It's gonna look incredible on
you.

544
01:14:42,826 --> 01:14:44,175
We're not married yet.

545
01:14:44,218 --> 01:14:45,481
No, but we're gonna be.

546
01:14:45,524 --> 01:14:47,308
That's why I gave you the ring,

547
01:14:47,352 --> 01:14:49,136
and that's why
I brought you over here.

548
01:14:49,180 --> 01:14:50,181
I'm gonna marry you.

549
01:14:51,356 --> 01:14:52,531
- When?
- As soon as I get the money.

550
01:14:52,575 --> 01:14:53,967
We're gonna have
that wedding you want,

551
01:14:54,011 --> 01:14:55,491
I'm gonna bring over
your mother and father.

552
01:14:55,534 --> 01:14:58,145
I'll bring over your whole
freakin' family if I can.

553
01:14:58,189 --> 01:14:59,712
As soon as I get it.

554
01:15:00,365 --> 01:15:01,671
Come on, try it on.

555
01:15:02,410 --> 01:15:04,543
Sorry, I can't...

556
01:15:04,848 --> 01:15:06,240
Not until we're married.

557
01:15:06,850 --> 01:15:07,546
Okay.

558
01:15:08,025 --> 01:15:09,026
I'll wait.

559
01:15:10,331 --> 01:15:12,377
But who's gonna sleep
on the bed? Me or you?

560
01:15:12,420 --> 01:15:12,943
You!

561
01:15:14,422 --> 01:15:16,033
No, no, no, I'll sleep
on the couch, you on the bed.

562
01:15:16,076 --> 01:15:17,861
No, I'll sleep on the floor!

563
01:15:18,078 --> 01:15:21,517
Well, I'd better start
getting used to the couch.

564
01:15:26,434 --> 01:15:28,001
[Telephone ringing.]

565
01:15:28,045 --> 01:15:29,699
Can you get that please?

566
01:15:38,403 --> 01:15:39,447
Hello?

567
01:15:42,059 --> 01:15:44,017
- Who's on the phone?
- A woman.

568
01:15:44,061 --> 01:15:45,845
I think it's your sister.

569
01:15:45,889 --> 01:15:47,107
She sounds angry.

570
01:15:47,151 --> 01:15:48,456
Just hang up.

571
01:16:06,997 --> 01:16:08,955
[Door bell ringing.]

572
01:16:14,265 --> 01:16:14,831
Tess!

573
01:16:15,440 --> 01:16:16,572
Dalisay!

574
01:16:17,747 --> 01:16:18,704
Condom?

575
01:16:18,748 --> 01:16:19,705
Fantasy?

576
01:16:19,749 --> 01:16:20,837
No problema.

577
01:16:22,142 --> 01:16:23,796
[Sound of subway 
moving overhead.]

578
01:16:24,928 --> 01:16:25,537
Your change.

579
01:16:26,320 --> 01:16:28,279
- Okay. Bye-bye!
- Adios!

580
01:16:32,283 --> 01:16:34,285
[speaking Tagalog]

581
01:16:41,509 --> 01:16:41,945
Nick!

582
01:16:42,946 --> 01:16:44,121
What's the matter?

583
01:16:44,512 --> 01:16:46,732
I think there's another
one outside. Look.

584
01:16:46,776 --> 01:16:49,517
What are you talking about,
another what?

585
01:16:51,781 --> 01:16:52,782
Shit!

586
01:16:54,218 --> 01:16:56,612
Now he's bringing the whole
goddamned family over!

587
01:18:44,763 --> 01:18:45,851
I'm ready.

588
01:18:45,895 --> 01:18:47,244
I feel great today!

589
01:18:48,288 --> 01:18:49,899
- Hello!
- Hi!

590
01:19:10,180 --> 01:19:11,790
What's so funny?

591
01:19:18,318 --> 01:19:20,277
What's that?
What do you mean?

592
01:19:21,104 --> 01:19:22,932
Dalisay said that you're...

593
01:19:25,935 --> 01:19:28,546
Ah, if the boys could
see me now.

594
01:19:30,113 --> 01:19:32,245
Can I ask you
a personal question?

595
01:19:32,289 --> 01:19:33,159
Sure!

596
01:19:33,203 --> 01:19:34,291
What do you wanna know?

597
01:19:35,814 --> 01:19:36,946
Are you serious about
your intentions with my cousin?

598
01:19:38,556 --> 01:19:40,297
About as serious as a heart
attack, that's pretty serious!

599
01:19:41,124 --> 01:19:43,082
I don't believe that.

600
01:19:43,126 --> 01:19:45,171
You hardly know each other!

601
01:19:45,563 --> 01:19:47,391
Well, I'll see you at the
wedding.

602
01:19:47,695 --> 01:19:49,567
To see is to believe.

603
01:19:50,960 --> 01:19:53,353
Look!
It's so beautiful!

604
01:19:59,229 --> 01:20:00,578
Your wish...

605
01:20:01,144 --> 01:20:02,580
is my command.

606
01:20:38,572 --> 01:20:39,704
Got it!

607
01:20:41,184 --> 01:20:42,707
I got it!

608
01:20:43,534 --> 01:20:44,578
Got it!

609
01:20:47,451 --> 01:20:50,367
♪ [Theme music comes up.]

610
01:20:52,195 --> 01:20:53,631
Dalisay!

611
01:21:14,130 --> 01:21:15,783
- Come on!
- No!

612
01:21:36,413 --> 01:21:38,589
So how come you never told me
about this before?

613
01:21:38,937 --> 01:21:40,199
I was ashamed.

614
01:21:40,243 --> 01:21:42,549
I wanted to tell you in person.

615
01:21:42,593 --> 01:21:44,900
And how much is
your sister's heart operation?

616
01:21:44,943 --> 01:21:46,902
100,000 pesos.

617
01:21:46,945 --> 01:21:48,555
So that makes it...

618
01:21:48,599 --> 01:21:49,600
$4,000 dollars.

619
01:21:49,948 --> 01:21:52,124
That's why I have to work.

620
01:21:52,429 --> 01:21:55,040
Dalisay, I didn't bring you
over here to work.

621
01:21:55,084 --> 01:21:58,391
But I don't want to depend on
you for my family problems.

622
01:21:58,435 --> 01:22:01,394
Why don't you let me be the one
to solve your problems?

623
01:22:01,438 --> 01:22:04,136
I don't want you to work, okay?

624
01:22:04,180 --> 01:22:08,053
Just do it my way and I'll take
care of everything, alright?

625
01:22:08,097 --> 01:22:09,011
Don't worry.

626
01:22:09,707 --> 01:22:11,448
Can I have my wallet please?

627
01:22:14,277 --> 01:22:15,539
Thank you.

628
01:22:30,380 --> 01:22:31,511
Twenty.

629
01:22:34,688 --> 01:22:35,907
Forty.

630
01:22:37,648 --> 01:22:38,954
Sixty.

631
01:22:40,825 --> 01:22:42,174
Eighty.

632
01:22:43,480 --> 01:22:44,829
One hundred.

633
01:22:46,004 --> 01:22:47,397
Twenty, forty.

634
01:22:48,572 --> 01:22:50,617
That's $140 dollars.

635
01:22:50,661 --> 01:22:53,664
That's everything that
I have in the world.

636
01:22:54,534 --> 01:22:55,971
It's for you.

637
01:22:58,538 --> 01:22:59,844
That's it.

638
01:23:00,497 --> 01:23:02,629
Come on, Phil, give me a break.

639
01:23:02,673 --> 01:23:06,590
I nearly tore down my whole
apartment for a measly $600.

640
01:23:06,851 --> 01:23:09,332
What do I look like?
A fucking bank?

641
01:23:09,723 --> 01:23:11,682
I don't have $2,000 to lend you.

642
01:23:12,030 --> 01:23:14,467
Yeah, but you don't understand.

643
01:23:14,511 --> 01:23:16,817
My girlfriend's family's
in a jam in Philippines,

644
01:23:16,861 --> 01:23:18,819
and it looks like
they're gonna lose everything.

645
01:23:18,863 --> 01:23:22,214
I gotta do something cause
I'm the only one who can help.

646
01:23:22,258 --> 01:23:23,999
Can you help me, please?

647
01:23:24,042 --> 01:23:26,044
Ever since you come here,

648
01:23:26,088 --> 01:23:28,177
it costs me nothing
but headaches.

649
01:23:28,699 --> 01:23:32,224
You come in here 4 fucking
months ago, begging for a job,

650
01:23:33,051 --> 01:23:34,313
I got out on a limb,

651
01:23:34,357 --> 01:23:37,360
against my better judgment
and I hire you.

652
01:23:39,362 --> 01:23:41,016
Look at your car!

653
01:23:41,059 --> 01:23:42,887
Go ahead, look at it.

654
01:23:43,366 --> 01:23:45,498
It's all banged to shit.

655
01:23:45,542 --> 01:23:48,023
You're lucky
you got this fucking job!

656
01:23:48,371 --> 01:23:50,155
Now do me a favor:

657
01:23:50,199 --> 01:23:52,375
Don't bust
my fucking balls anymore!

658
01:23:53,071 --> 01:23:53,985
If you need money,

659
01:23:55,334 --> 01:23:56,770
you go outside,
and you bust somebody else's.

660
01:23:57,075 --> 01:23:58,729
[Hard knocking on door.]

661
01:24:03,212 --> 01:24:05,736
So you're the one my cousin
was telling me about.

662
01:24:05,779 --> 01:24:06,606
Who are you?

663
01:24:06,650 --> 01:24:07,694
Who am I?

664
01:24:07,738 --> 01:24:08,782
Who the hell are you?

665
01:24:09,131 --> 01:24:11,263
Who said
you could paint my apartment?

666
01:24:11,307 --> 01:24:13,439
You got some nerve
hanging up on me.

667
01:24:13,483 --> 01:24:16,747
- Where's my brother?
- I'm sorry he's not here.

668
01:24:21,273 --> 01:24:22,796
I can't believe
you're asking me this.

669
01:24:22,840 --> 01:24:24,189
You're not even supposed
to be down here.

670
01:24:24,233 --> 01:24:25,973
I got nowhere else to go, Alma.

671
01:24:26,017 --> 01:24:27,627
Nick would kill me!

672
01:24:27,671 --> 01:24:30,065
Don't worry,
I'm gonna pay you back.

673
01:24:30,108 --> 01:24:32,545
It's not the money,
I'm worried about, it's Nick.

674
01:24:32,589 --> 01:24:34,417
Alma, please!

675
01:24:40,162 --> 01:24:41,946
- Get out!
- But why?

676
01:24:41,989 --> 01:24:42,773
You want to know why?

677
01:24:43,991 --> 01:24:44,688
We had an agreement,
my brother broke it!

678
01:24:46,081 --> 01:24:46,255
He's not supposed to be
living in this apartment,

679
01:24:46,951 --> 01:24:47,256
and neither are you.

680
01:24:47,778 --> 01:24:48,518
So get out!

681
01:24:49,475 --> 01:24:50,607
I can't believe I'm doing this.

682
01:24:51,999 --> 01:24:53,784
Don't worry, I'm not gonna
tell a soul, alright?

683
01:24:53,827 --> 01:24:55,786
I'm gonna pay you back and...

684
01:24:56,047 --> 01:24:57,962
[Bell ringing on shop door.]

685
01:25:03,663 --> 01:25:05,230
- Cash, right?
- Yes...

686
01:25:05,274 --> 01:25:07,276
What the hell is going on here?

687
01:25:08,799 --> 01:25:11,106
Nick, I could explain...

688
01:25:11,149 --> 01:25:13,934
- Okay? - You were gonna give
him $2,000?

689
01:25:13,978 --> 01:25:16,589
- Why is my wife giving you
money? - Nick, let me explain!

690
01:25:16,633 --> 01:25:19,331
This guy screws up all our
plans, and gonna give him money!

691
01:25:20,158 --> 01:25:21,638
[Shop bell ringing.]

692
01:25:21,986 --> 01:25:23,292
What are you doing?

693
01:25:23,640 --> 01:25:25,163
What's going on?
What are you doing out here?

694
01:25:25,207 --> 01:25:26,295
Just let me go.

695
01:25:27,818 --> 01:25:28,601
- What are you talking about?
- Hey, you forgot this.

696
01:25:28,645 --> 01:25:29,472
Stop it!

697
01:25:30,212 --> 01:25:31,038
Son-of-a-bitch!

698
01:25:32,475 --> 01:25:34,172
- I'm not gonna let you get
away! - What going on here?

699
01:25:34,216 --> 01:25:36,783
Don't you ever set foot
inside this store again!

700
01:25:36,827 --> 01:25:38,959
As far as I'm concerned,
we're not family anymore!

701
01:25:39,003 --> 01:25:40,439
You'd better find yourself
a good lawyer!

702
01:25:40,483 --> 01:25:41,571
Get back inside!

703
01:25:42,180 --> 01:25:43,050
Take it easy!

704
01:25:44,051 --> 01:25:45,314
Hey you!

705
01:25:45,662 --> 01:25:47,838
Welcome to America.

706
01:25:47,881 --> 01:25:49,013
Don't listen to her.

707
01:25:50,580 --> 01:25:51,929
Come on upstairs and I'll
explain the whole thing to you.

708
01:25:52,234 --> 01:25:54,323
[Sound of Jan's car 
accelerating.]

709
01:25:56,194 --> 01:25:58,849
[Metal door closing, 
subway clanging overhead.]

710
01:27:09,920 --> 01:27:11,400
What's wrong?

711
01:27:12,096 --> 01:27:14,054
My parents want to know

712
01:27:14,098 --> 01:27:17,144
when I'm going to
start sending them more money.

713
01:27:18,755 --> 01:27:21,323
I thought we just
sent them money.

714
01:27:21,671 --> 01:27:24,456
But that was over
three weeks ago.

715
01:27:25,588 --> 01:27:28,808
I know,
but we sent them $1,000.

716
01:27:29,418 --> 01:27:31,246
But that's not enough.

717
01:27:31,594 --> 01:27:33,509
I know it's not enough,

718
01:27:34,118 --> 01:27:36,076
but I'm doing the best I can.

719
01:27:36,120 --> 01:27:38,775
I'm sending them every penny
I'm making.

720
01:27:39,645 --> 01:27:41,430
I don't know what else to do.

721
01:27:41,473 --> 01:27:42,518
I know.

722
01:27:44,128 --> 01:27:45,303
I'm just afraid that by the time
you send them all the money,

723
01:27:45,347 --> 01:27:47,174
it will be too late.

724
01:27:48,959 --> 01:27:50,003
Too late?

725
01:27:51,614 --> 01:27:53,311
Too late for what?

726
01:27:54,791 --> 01:27:56,836
Can I talk to Tess?

727
01:27:57,359 --> 01:27:59,752
Why do you want to talk to Tess?

728
01:27:59,796 --> 01:28:01,798
She said she can help.

729
01:28:03,147 --> 01:28:05,454
Am I not doing enough?

730
01:28:06,629 --> 01:28:09,284
I don't understand why
you have to talk to Tess.

731
01:28:09,327 --> 01:28:10,633
I'm doing all I can.

732
01:28:10,676 --> 01:28:12,112
I'm sorry.

733
01:28:12,156 --> 01:28:15,159
I'm sorry for giving you
all these problems.

734
01:28:17,857 --> 01:28:20,207
You're not giving me
any problems...

735
01:28:20,251 --> 01:28:21,992
They're little problems.

736
01:28:22,471 --> 01:28:24,299
I'll make money, I'll get them
money.

737
01:28:24,342 --> 01:28:27,040
and we'll get them
out of the way and...

738
01:28:27,345 --> 01:28:29,652
My sister is in the hospital.

739
01:28:34,091 --> 01:28:35,832
What does that mean?

740
01:28:37,224 --> 01:28:40,489
My parents want to know
when I'm going to send them

741
01:28:40,532 --> 01:28:42,839
more money for the operation.

742
01:28:46,364 --> 01:28:48,323
I don't believe this.

743
01:28:49,367 --> 01:28:51,326
What should I tell to them?

744
01:28:52,022 --> 01:28:54,241
What should you tell to them?

745
01:28:55,068 --> 01:28:58,507
You should tell them,
"One problem at a time."

746
01:29:05,383 --> 01:29:06,776
I'm going out.

747
01:29:08,691 --> 01:29:11,041
What should I tell my parents?

748
01:29:12,434 --> 01:29:13,913
Well, Dalisay...

749
01:29:14,871 --> 01:29:17,526
You can tell them that in
America,

750
01:29:17,961 --> 01:29:20,355
money doesn't grow on trees.

751
01:29:21,573 --> 01:29:22,444
So...

752
01:29:23,053 --> 01:29:25,055
I'm gonna make some.

753
01:29:27,797 --> 01:29:29,538
[Sound of door slamming.]

754
01:29:42,072 --> 01:29:44,379
[Sound of bar door 
slapping closed.]

755
01:29:46,163 --> 01:29:49,035
[Sound of radio announcer 
at sports event.]

756
01:29:49,079 --> 01:29:50,080
Boo!

757
01:29:52,778 --> 01:29:54,737
You gonna buy me that drink?

758
01:29:56,086 --> 01:29:57,261
Go ahead.

759
01:29:58,088 --> 01:30:00,438
Knock yourself out.

760
01:30:01,744 --> 01:30:03,920
You look like you already have.

761
01:30:05,138 --> 01:30:07,271
As a matter of fact,
I haven't.

762
01:30:09,491 --> 01:30:12,363
Then you look like
you could use some company.

763
01:30:15,366 --> 01:30:18,282
Where have you been?
I haven't seen you around.

764
01:30:18,935 --> 01:30:21,198
Digging myself into a hole.

765
01:30:24,201 --> 01:30:25,376
Ooooohh...

766
01:30:26,508 --> 01:30:28,945
Get the heater on,
my ass is freezing!

767
01:30:28,988 --> 01:30:30,599
Hang on, hang on.

768
01:30:37,214 --> 01:30:39,825
I can't stand it,
I'm too fucking cold!

769
01:30:39,869 --> 01:30:41,000
C'mon, warm me up!

770
01:30:42,132 --> 01:30:43,089
- Please warm me up.
- Hold on, hold on!

771
01:30:43,133 --> 01:30:45,440
Hold on! Be careful!

772
01:30:46,963 --> 01:30:49,792
[Sound of tow truck.]

773
01:31:11,074 --> 01:31:12,554
Just tell me one thing:

774
01:31:13,990 --> 01:31:15,818
What the fuck were you thinking
about when this happened?

775
01:31:19,517 --> 01:31:22,389
If I were you,
I'd get another job.

776
01:31:22,999 --> 01:31:25,305
Because you ain't gonna drive
another taxi...

777
01:31:25,349 --> 01:31:27,264
Not as long as I can help it!

778
01:31:34,837 --> 01:31:36,839
[Dalisay speaking Tagalog 
on phone.]

779
01:32:32,416 --> 01:32:35,898
My parents called collect
from the hospital.

780
01:32:46,996 --> 01:32:49,128
My sister's very sick.

781
01:32:55,918 --> 01:32:57,876
I'll pay you
for the telephone calls

782
01:32:57,920 --> 01:32:59,922
as soon as I get the money.

783
01:33:04,927 --> 01:33:06,450
I got fired!

784
01:33:07,625 --> 01:33:09,453
I don't have a job anymore.

785
01:33:27,950 --> 01:33:30,126
I'm going to Tess tomorrow.

786
01:33:32,128 --> 01:33:33,172
What for?

787
01:33:35,000 --> 01:33:36,611
